table.name: ad_positions
table.Comment: The following table specifies the position of the ad as a relative measure of visibility or prominence. This OpenRTB table has values derived from the IAB Quality Assurance Guidelines (QAG). Practitioners should keep in sync with updates to the QAG values as published on IAB.net. Values “3” – “6” apply to apps per the mobile addendum to QAG version 1.5.

table.name: ad_types
table.Comment: The different ad sizes that are available in the ad server. These should confirm to IAB ad types.

table.name: advertisement_price_types
table.Comment: Represents the different types of pricing in the system, such as CPM, CPA, CPC.

table.name: advertisers
table.Comment: Represents an advertiser that will have many aorders, acamps, creatives.

table.name: aorders
table.Comment: This represents an advertiser order. An order provides a means to manage a group of campaigns.

table.name: assigned_advertiser_content_categories
table.Comment: Represents the assignment of content categories to advertisers.

table.name: assigned_creatives_mimes
table.Comment: Although not required, some RTB Bid Requests provide a white lists of MIME types allowed for the response. This table allows for a creative to be categorized by its MIME type.

table.name: assigned_roles
table.Comment: The roles that are assigned to a user.

table.name: banner_ad_types
table.Comment: The types of ads that can be accepted by the exchange unless restricted by publisher site settings

table.name: bid_locations
table.Comment: The locations on an exchange to buy or sell impressions.

table.name: contacts
table.Comment: The contact person for an advertiser.

table.name: content_categories
table.Comment: The content categories as defined by the IAB. Provides a node data-structure for IAB’s contextual taxonomy for categorization. Standard IDs have been adopted to easily support the communication of primary and secondary categories for various objects.

table.name: currencies
table.Comment: A listing of the world currencies.

table.name: impression_price_types
table.Comment: Represents the different types of impression pricing in the system, such as CPM, RS.

table.name: mime_types
table.Comment: The listing of mime types, such as, but not limited to “image/jpg”, “image/gif” and “application/x-shockwave-flash”.

table.name: picking_algorithms
table.Comment: This table represents the various picking algorithms that are available to the ad platform.

table.name: picking_algorithms_h
table.Comment: The audit table for the algorithms table.

table.name: roles
table.Comment: The roles that are allowed for login users.

table.name: schema_migrations
table.Comment: Used to managed schema migrations. Although a schema manager is not currently used.

table.name: supported_targeting_ops
table.Comment: Associates which targeting operations are supported by a targeting type.

table.name: usernames
table.Comment: The username for logging into the UI or an APP id for UIDLOG auditing.
